# Material You UI

This project follows **Material You (Material Design 3)** for UI.

## Brand palette (NSLAW)

Bảng màu thương hiệu là **xanh lá đậm + gold** (theo logo NSLAW), khai báo tập trung
bằng CSS vars trong `src/app/globals.css`:

- `--primary: #14532d` (xanh lá đậm) — dùng qua `bg-primary` / `text-primary`...
- `--accent: #9a7b16` (gold, đủ tương phản để làm chữ) + `--accent-muted: #f6edcf`
- Radius phẳng/sharp: `--radius-md: 0.375rem` (6px) là mặc định; ưu tiên `rounded-md`.
- Shadow overlay thống nhất: `var(--shadow-overlay)` (dùng cho modal/panel/menu nổi).

Không hardcode hex navy cũ (`#152d4f`, `#0f2138`, `#3b82c4`); luôn dùng token/primary.
Logo đặt tại `public/logo-nslaw.png` (login + header sidebar).

## Do

- Prefer toned surfaces, soft tonal fills, and clear hierarchy over heavy decoration
- Use color to convey meaning (status, emphasis) with readable contrast
- Prefer light elevation: thin borders / surface tint; avoid flashy glow and multi-layer colored drop shadows
- Keep interactive chrome simple: chips/tags, clean menus, restrained motion
- Status / chips: flat tonal pill (filled or soft container), no colored outer glow
- Dropdowns/menus: compact, quiet list — white/surface background, hairline divider optional, soft hover, no loud option background blocks

## Don't

- Colored `box-shadow` / neon glow on chips, badges, or buttons (except brief success feedback when explicitly requested)
- Heavy `shadow-lg` + saturated option rows that fight the rest of the UI
- Overbuilt cards with multi-layer shadows for decoration

## Status colors (example)

Use saturated fill on the active tag; keep the open menu plain (label + subtle hover):

- NEW — sky / info tonal
- IN_PROGRESS — amber / caution tonal
- ON_HOLD — rose / pause tonal  
- CLOSED — emerald / success tonal
